## Phase 4 — Build the lower-variance FINALS profile

The qualifier is Swiss/cumulative over 400-hand matches (variance-friendly, skill
rewarded). The finals are **single-elimination** — variance is the enemy, because
the best bot still loses ~30%+ of individual matches to a worse one on a bad run.
Your `aggro_heavy` 46% win rate is the canary: a +EV but coinflip-win-rate profile
gets knocked out of a bracket.

This is a **config switch, not new code** — a flag set layered on the combined bot:

| Setting | Qualifier profile | Finals profile |
|---|---|---|
| V5a anti-perma | on, normal margin | **on, tighter** (avoid all marginal stack-offs) |
| V5c anti-folder | normal cap | **lower freq cap / bigger safety margin** (fewer bluffs = lower variance) |
| Marginal stack-offs | take +EV spots | **decline thin coinflips** you don't need |
| V5b anti-station | unchanged | unchanged (value extraction is low-variance) |

Expose it as a single constant (e.g. `_PROFILE = "qualifier" | "finals"`) that
sets the caps. A/B the finals profile vs the qualifier profile on `aggro_heavy`
and `tight_heavy`: you're looking for the finals profile to **raise win rate**
(and tighten the CI) even if it costs a little mean Δ. That trade is correct for
a bracket and wrong for the Swiss — hence two profiles.

