## Decision flow (compressed)

```
A/B each of V5a/b/c vs frozen V4.1 on real eval7
        │
        ▼
Phase 0: apply pre-committed keep/reject/tune criteria per module
        │
   ┌────┴─────┐
 TUNE       KEEP/REJECT
   │           │
Phase 2     Phase 1: combine survivors → re-A/B combined on ALL 5 fields
(one pass)     │
   └────┬──────┘
        ▼
Phase 3: build D1 patch-window pipeline   ◄── highest leverage, before Day 1
        ▼
Phase 4: build finals (low-variance) profile
        ▼
Phase 6: robustness + timeout safety on real eval7
        ▼
   (Phase 5 raise-respect only if time remains)
        ▼
   SUBMIT
```

## Priority order if you are short on time

1. **Phase 0 + Phase 1** (decide, combine, verify the combined bot) — you must
   have one trustworthy bot.
2. **Phase 6** (robustness/timeout on real eval7) — an untested-for-timeout bot
   can lose silently regardless of strategy.
3. **Phase 3** (patch pipeline) — the edge the field neglects; where winning
   happens.
4. **Phase 4** (finals profile) — needed the moment you reach the bracket.
5. **Phase 5** (raise-respect) — only if everything above is done and verified.

Everything past Phase 4 is upside. Everything through Phase 4 is the difference
between a bot that *is* good and a bot you can *prove* is good under tournament
conditions — and only the second kind wins.
